# Testing and CI

- Every new feature ships with at least one unit test (Vitest + Testing
  Library) and, when it touches the journey, a Playwright e2e for the happy
  path. Vitest config: `apps/web/vitest.config.ts`.
- Highest-value unit targets (coverage ~90% on `src/lib/riasec/`): scoring
  determinism (property-based — every answer set yields a valid 3-letter
  code; ties resolve R→I→A→S→E→C), the strand-validation matrix (all 7
  strands × verdicts, GAS special case), and the store's re-answer
  subtraction logic.
- RPC contract tests run `supabase start` against real migrations + seed and
  assert `match_courses` ranking semantics, so SQL and TypeScript never drift.
- E2E journeys: land → profile → full quiz → results → export/email (Resend
  mocked); mid-quiz refresh → resume; route guards and invalid-email paths.
- Visual regression: Playwright `toHaveScreenshot` on key pages, light + dark,
  under `reducedMotion: 'reduce'` emulation; snapshots compared on Linux CI
  only.
- Lighthouse CI gate ≥ 90 (Performance/Accessibility/SEO, mobile emulation)
  on every PR.
- Use fixtures and the generated `supabase/seed.sql` for reproducible data.
- CI (GitHub Actions) runs typecheck, lint, unit tests, and build on every PR.
- Name tests by behavior, not implementation.
